<plot>Roland wanted to make his mother proud by becoming a blood donor. However, at his first try he got rejected... Roland is gay and gay men are not allowed to donate blood in Belgium. 'For this is my blood' is one man's quest for answers. Why is he not allowed to donate? Is this a case of discrimination? Is every gay men a threat? This documentary is a global journey for the truth. Sometimes comical, sometimes bloody serious... And then Roland found something that could change the rules...</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?199917</url></doc>
